1. e4 e5 {This is how we do it! We shall cover all the good, bad and ugly 
choices White has after this. The following is just a sneak preview into some of 
the lines.} 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6 4. Ba4 Nf6 5. O-O Be7 6. Re1 b5 7. Bb3 O-O 8. 
c3 d5 9. exd5 Nxd5 10. Nxe5 Nxe5 11. Rxe5 c6 12. d4 Bd6 13. Re1 Qh4 14. g3 Qh3 
15. Re4 {[%cal Ge4h4][%csl Rh4,Rh3] This move looks very random, but 
understanding it and the ideas behind it and Black's reply will help you make 
sense of why people do what in the Marshall. As for the relevance of 15. Re4, 
play is sharp, but Black is OK without being down to only moves, so I don't 
expect Re4 to come back into fashion anytime soon. So, White wants to go Rh4 and 
push our Queen back. What to do?} g5 {[%cal Gg5h4,Re4h4][%csl Rh4] Stopping Rh4 
using a little tactic. The pawn might also assist a quick attack in the form of 
*f5-f4.*} 16. Qf3 Bf5 {[%csl Re4]} 17. Bc2 {This line just doesn't work.} Bxe4 
18. Bxe4 Qe6 {[%cal Bf7f5]} 19. Bxg5 f5 20. Bd3 f4 21. Qe4 Qd7 $1 22. Nd2 Rae8 
23. Qh1 Qg7 *

