1. e4 e5 {This is how we do it! We shall cover all the good, bad and ugly 
choices White has after this. The following is just a sneak preview into some of 
the lines.} 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Nc3 Nf6 4. d4 exd4 5. Nxd4 Bb4 {By far the main move. 
Pinning, developing, preparing to castle.} 6. Nxc6 {The only decent move.} bxc6 
7. Bd3 d5 8. exd5 O-O $5 {Gambitting the pawn just for show. cxd5 usually 
transposes back.} 9. O-O Bg4 $1 {Avoiding the dull cxd5 positions. Introduced by 
the strong Indian theoretician Vidit against Wei Yi in 2018. The only problem is 
